<tr>
<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=harlequinn&Board=bards&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Harlequinn (harlequinn) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 "> | </font><a href="mailto:jamesbranch@worldnet.att.net" OnMouseOver="window.status='Send email to Harlequinn.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Email</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">It's really not that difficult once you get the hang of it...here goes:<p>

create hotkeys for each of the songs that you want in your twist sequence.  some bards i know keep instrument specific songs on separate pages, but not me.  in my sequence i have (hotkey #1) hymn of healing, (2) verses of celerity, (3) bellow or dot song, (4) snare song, (5) selos fast feet, and (6) fear song usually.  On my second hotkey page i have (1) charm and (2) mana song.  also on my second page i have created hotkeys for pet commands for charmed creatures because in a lot of cases you can charm and command a mob to stay put and run off.  anyway back to twisting...most songs have a pulse time of about 3 to 5 seconds..once you see the icon for the song appear simply tap the new song twice to get it going..once it starts move on to the next one.  you should start off with twisting 2 songs and eventually you will get to 3,4 or even 5 (so i have heard) but this is based upon lag and mobs attacking you.  in a general combat i am twisting heal, celerity and dot song until mobs run and i hit them with snare song.  it is important to set up the keys in a convenient way and this is why my #1,#2 and #3 are where they are...they are my most used.  This same tactic is used for kiting...as you may have noticed i have dot at #3, snare song at #4 and selos at #5.  With this i can dot, snare a mob and keep selos on by hitting hotkeys 3,4 and 5.  All songs dont have a 3 to 5 second pulse so you will have to experiment a bit but when all is said and done twisting is a valuable (and necessary) tool for us bards.<p>

Harlequinn Drumrunner<br>
Bard of the 40th Song<br>
Brell Server</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
